{"metadata":{"title":"OmniLight3D","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"OmniLight3D"}],"symbolKind":"class","externalID":"s:10SwiftGodot11OmniLight3DC","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"OmniLight3D"}],"role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"SwiftGodot"}],"roleHeading":"Class"},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"relationshipsSections":[{"kind":"relationships","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Light3D"],"type":"inheritsFrom","title":"Inherits From"},{"title":"Conforms To","kind":"relationships","type":"conformsTo","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/GodotObject","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/s23CustomStringConvertibleP","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/SQ","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/SH","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/s12IdentifiableP","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/VariantRepresentable","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/VariantStorable"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot"]]},"kind":"symbol","sections":[],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/OmniLight3D","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Omnidirectional light, such as a light bulb or a candle."}],"topicSections":[{"title":"Instance Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/OmniLight3D\/omniAttenuation","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/OmniLight3D\/omniRange","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/OmniLight3D\/omniShadowMode"]},{"title":"Type Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/OmniLight3D\/godotClassName"]},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/OmniLight3D\/ShadowMode"],"title":"Enumerations"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"OmniLight3D"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","type":"heading","anchor":"overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"An Omnidirectional light is a type of ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Light3D"},{"text":" that emits light in all directions. The light is attenuated by distance and this attenuation can be configured by changing its energy, radius, and attenuation parameters.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When using the Mobile rendering method, only 8 omni lights can be displayed on each mesh resource. Attempting to display more than 8 omni lights on a single mesh resource will result in omni lights flickering in and out as the camera moves. When using the Compatibility rendering method, only 8 omni lights can be displayed on each mesh resource by default, but this can be increased by adjusting "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ProjectSettings\/rendering\/limits\/opengl\/maxLightsPerObject"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}],"style":"note","name":"Note","type":"aside"},{"type":"aside","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When using the Mobile or Compatibility rendering methods, omni lights will only correctly affect meshes whose visibility AABB intersects with the light’s AABB. If using a shader to deform the mesh in a way that makes it go outside its AABB, "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/GeometryInstance3D\/extraCullMargin","isActive":true},{"text":" must be increased on the mesh. Otherwise, the light may not be visible on the mesh.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Note","style":"note"}]}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/omnilight3d"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"references":{"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/Variant":{"fragments":[{"